description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for the position of full time Clinical Lead Nurse within Mental Health Older Persons Services on Moor Croft Ward at the newly commissioned Foss Park Hospital in York. The post is on an 18 bedded mixed gender ward for individuals with a functional mental illness. The post holder will work as part of the multi-disciplinary team delivering high quality, patient focused care in collaboration with family and in conjunction with partnership working. In a 18 new York Hospital &#39;Foss Park&#39; in April 2020. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting and challenging role and will afford the opportunity to work as part of a supportive team that is focused on delivering high standards of care through evidenced based practice. As a Band 6 Nurse, you will work closely with patients and their relatives/ carers as part of a multi-disciplinary team to help plan, develop and implement behaviour support plans within a well-being focused model of working. You will also support and supervise staff within the multi-disciplinary team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. Experience of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;working in a multidisciplinary mental health setting &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;is&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; required for this post. We are looking for someone who is motivated, enthusiastic and compassionate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be required to work as part of a shift pattern that will cover both days and nights.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jonathan Conyers, Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;jonathan.conyers@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01904461140&lt;/p&gt;
